---
const { content } = Astro.props;
const title = content?.title?.replace(/\s*-?\s*Best Food Today/gi, "");
---

<div class="bg-white py-12">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="bg-white px-6 py-16 sm:py-32 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-gray-700">
        <h1
          class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-center text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl"
        >
          Cookie Policy
        </h1>

        <p class="mt-6">
          This Cookie Policy explains how {title} and its affiliates
          (collectively, "we," "our," or "us") use cookies and similar tracking
          technologies on our website. It should be read together with our
          Privacy Policy.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6">This policy is effective as of June 30, 2026.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">Last updated: June 30, 2026</p>

        <!-- What Are Cookies -->
        <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
          What Are Cookies?
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6">
          Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device when you
          visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work, to
          improve their performance, and to provide information to the site
          owners and third parties. "Similar technologies" include pixels, tags,
          and software development kits (SDKs) that work in much the same way.
        </p>

        {content?.tag && (
        <>
        <!-- How We Use Cookies -->
        <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
          How We Use Cookies
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6">We use cookies and similar technologies for:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
          <li>
            <strong>Essential cookies</strong> — required for the website to
            function and to keep it secure.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — to understand how visitors use
            our website so we can improve it.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Advertising cookies</strong> — to deliver and measure
            advertising, and to understand the effectiveness of our advertising
            campaigns across other websites and platforms.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Advertising and Analytics Partners -->
        <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
          Advertising and Analytics Partners
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6">
          To promote our restaurant and measure how our advertising performs, we
          may allow the following third-party platforms to set cookies and
          similar identifiers on our website. Depending on how this website is
          configured, these partners may collect information about your visit
          and use it to deliver and measure advertising on their own and other
          websites:
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          Google (Google Ads, Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager)
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may use Google services to manage tags, measure website traffic,
          and run and measure Google Ads campaigns (including conversion
          tracking and remarketing). You can control the ads Google shows you
          and opt out of personalized advertising through
          <a
            href="https://adssettings.google.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a
          >, and you can opt out of Google Analytics using the
          <a
            href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a
          >.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          Meta (Facebook and Instagram Ads)
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may use the Meta Pixel to measure the effectiveness of our
          advertising on Facebook and Instagram and to show ads to people who
          have visited our website. You can manage your ad preferences in your
          <a
            href="https://www.facebook.com/settings?tab=ads"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Facebook ad settings</a
          > and your Instagram account settings.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
          TikTok Ads
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may use the TikTok Pixel to measure and optimize our advertising
          campaigns on TikTok and to reach people who have visited our website.
          You can manage your ad preferences in your TikTok account settings
          under "Privacy" and "Ads."
        </p>

        <p class="mt-6">
          These partners act as independent controllers of the data they
          collect through these technologies. We encourage you to review their
          respective privacy and cookie policies to understand how they process
          your information.
        </p>

        <!-- Managing Cookies -->
        <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
          How to Manage or Disable Cookies
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6">
          Most browsers automatically accept cookies by default, but you can set
          your browser to remove or reject cookies through its settings. Please
          keep in mind that removing or blocking cookies may affect your
          experience and cause some features of the website to work incorrectly
          or become unavailable.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6">
          You can also opt out of interest-based advertising from many companies
          through these industry tools:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://optout.aboutads.info"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Digital Advertising Alliance (DAA)</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Network Advertising Initiative (NAI)</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Your Online Choices (EU)</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        </>
        )}

        <!-- Changes -->
        <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
          Changes to This Cookie Policy
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6">
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes
          in the technologies we use or for other operational, legal, or
          regulatory reasons. Any changes will be posted on this page.
        </p>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
          Contact Us
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-6">
          If you have any questions about our use of cookies, you may contact us
          using the following details:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6">
          <p class="mt-2">{title}</p>
          {content?.tel && <p class="mt-2">{"Tel: " + content.tel}</p>}
          {content?.email && <p class="mt-2">{"Email: " + content.email}</p>}
          {content?.address && (
            <p class="mt-2">{"Address: " + content.address}</p>
          )}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
